        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 8:55PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 855 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles east of Etowah, or 14 miles south of Madisonville, moving east
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Citico, Tellico Plains, and Coker Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM EDT for
southwestern North Carolina...and east Tennessee.</instruction>
